Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["5b. Static Eshelby Depolarization Tensor", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0d789514-e193-422f-9eec-468dabb12efa"],

Cell["\<\
The smooth polynomial misses the static (1/r) singular part. Via the \
divergence theorem, the PV volume integral becomes a regular surface integral \
over the cube faces: I^stat_{ijkl} = \[ContourIntegral] n_l \
\[PartialD]G^Kelvin_{ij}/\[PartialD]x_k dS.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aaee2bc9-974e-47e3-b8f7-1133a432cdf4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* Static Kelvin Green's tensor: G_{ij} = a0/r \[Delta]_{ij} + b0 x_i x_j/r^3 \
*)
a0stat = (\[Alpha]^2 + \[Beta]^2)/(8 Pi \[Rho] \[Alpha]^2 \[Beta]^2);
b0stat = (\[Alpha]^2 - \[Beta]^2)/(8 Pi \[Rho] \[Alpha]^2 \[Beta]^2);

Print[\"Static Green's tensor coefficients:\"];
Print[\"a0 = \", a0stat];
Print[\"b0 = \", b0stat];\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[87]:=",ExpressionUUID->"1f3c343f-ff45-4599-8800-15a491edfc6a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData["\<\"Static Green's tensor coefficients:\"\>"], "Print",
